the audit's been cleared.

941
01:04:00,940 --> 01:04:04,818
- Nick sent the papers. Everyone's happy.
- Thanks, Ron.

942
01:04:04,899 --> 01:04:09,211
Technically we've breached SIMEX rules,
but it was just a non-transaction.

943
01:04:09,299 --> 01:04:10,857
With any luck...

944
01:04:10,939 --> 01:04:15,409
...the auditors won't mention it, or we may
have problems with the local regulator.

945
01:04:15,498 --> 01:04:17,728
Sounds sensible.

946
01:04:17,818 --> 01:04:22,811
Do you know, Nick made $10 million
doing arbitrage in a week?

947
01:04:22,897 --> 01:04:25,650
That's about...
half a billion dollars a year.

948
01:04:25,737 --> 01:04:27,807
The guy's a turbo arbitrageur!

949
01:04:27,897 --> 01:04:31,684
If he's doing that amount of business
for that amount of profit,...

950
01:04:31,776 --> 01:04:35,405
...why don't we shut down the rest
of the bank? We're just overhead.

951
01:04:35,496 --> 01:04:37,054
Yeah!

952
01:04:47,055 --> 01:04:49,125
- Hello?
- Nick,...

953
01:04:49,215 --> 01:04:52,047
...are you avoiding me?
I've been trying you for days.

954
01:04:52,134 --> 01:04:53,931
Sorry, Tony, it's been chaos.

955
01:04:54,014 --> 01:04:56,403
The audit went through.
I thought you knew.

956
01:04:56,494 --> 01:04:59,486
- It's this SLK thing.
- It's all been cleared up.

957
01:05:00,173 --> 01:05:04,769
I know. What's bothering me is where
you got all the money to actually...

958
01:05:04,853 --> 01:05:06,809
...well, pay SLK in the first place.

959
01:05:06,893 --> 01:05:09,361
I mean, it's the equivalent
of $78 million!

960
01:05:09,452 --> 01:05:11,443
It doesn't add up, you know.

961
01:05:12,652 --> 01:05:17,521
It's obvious. It's part of the funding we've
had from you over the past few weeks.

962
01:05:17,612 --> 01:05:18,647
Yes.

963
01:05:18,732 --> 01:05:22,121
So, the same figure
will flow back to you.

964
01:05:22,211 --> 01:05:26,443
I see. You're saying that some of
the funding was used to pay SLK?

965
01:05:26,531 --> 01:05:30,000
That's right, Tony. So we'll
be able to pay it back to you.

966
01:05:30,090 --> 01:05:33,366
That'll be good. Er... getting
our funding down will be good.

967
01:05:33,450 --> 01:05:35,680
I'm having to juggle
quite a few balls.

968
01:05:35,770 --> 01:05:37,886
We all are, Tony.
Look, I've got to dash.

969
01:05:37,970 --> 01:05:39,766
I've got company for dinner.

970
01:05:39,849 --> 01:05:42,647
Of course.
Thanks, Nick.

971
01:05:42,729 --> 01:05:44,720
Thanks for... clearing that up.

972
01:05:51,328 --> 01:05:53,284
Yes, Ron.
What do you want?

973
01:05:53,368 --> 01:05:56,041
It's me, you wanker!
Danny.

974
01:05:56,128 --> 01:05:59,642
Bubble? What are you doing
calling me in the middle of the night?

975
01:05:59,727 --> 01:06:01,604
Are you anywhere near a TV?

976
01:06:01,687 --> 01:06:03,882
I suggest you tune in to CNN.

977
01:06:08,766 --> 01:06:11,963
The worst damage was in
the seaport of Kobe.

978
01:06:12,046 --> 01:06:14,355
Road and rail links are shattered...

979
01:06:15,086 --> 01:06:18,077
Jesus, an earthquake!
That's all we fuckin' need.

980
01:06:19,485 --> 01:06:21,476
This is gonna kill the market, man.

981
01:06:21,565 --> 01:06:24,398
The Nikkei's gonna fall
through the fuckin' floor!

982
01:06:24,485 --> 01:06:26,793
...milling around in search of help.

983
01:06:26,884 --> 01:06:30,001
Rescue operations are going
to be complicated, long...

984
01:06:30,084 --> 01:06:34,760
...and expensive. Mike Chinoy,
CNN, reporting live from Tokyo.

985
01:06:57,321 --> 01:07:01,155
Market's down 300 points, you stand
there cool as a fuckin' cucumber.

986
01:07:01,241 --> 01:07:03,311
The way I see it,
it's an opportunity.

987
01:07:03,401 --> 01:07:07,632
I'm gonna buy into the market.
Buy it all the way back up to 19,000.

988
01:07:07,720 --> 01:07:08,994
Oi!

989
01:07:12,320 --> 01:07:15,516
Fuckin' true what they say
about your gonads, mate.

990
01:07:16,559 --> 01:07:18,550
See what I mean?

991
01:07:19,559 --> 01:07:24,154
Think I'll give Fernando a bell in Tokyo,
see what's shakin'. No pun intended.

992
01:07:24,238 --> 01:07:26,627
It's Nick.
What's the situation in Kobe?

993
01:07:26,718 --> 01:07:30,791
We've been trying to contact our friends,
but the lines are down.

994
01:07:30,878 --> 01:07:32,788
Hold it a second.
We got movement.

995
01:07:32,877 --> 01:07:36,108
Holy shit, selling!
There's some selling!

996
01:07:36,917 --> 01:07:38,953
Fuckin' hell, it's in free fall!

997
01:07:39,037 --> 01:07:41,028
I've never seen it move so fast.

998
01:07:42,157 --> 01:07:45,068
350! 350!

999
01:07:45,156 --> 01:07:46,475
350!

1000
01:07:57,955 --> 01:08:00,025
Nick?

1001
01:08:00,115 --> 01:08:02,105
Sure you don't want us to stay?

1002
01:08:03,634 --> 01:08:05,590
No, I... I'm fine.
You go.

1003
01:08:05,674 --> 01:08:07,744
You'll make it right, Nick.

1004
01:08:08,354 --> 01:08:10,231
We all believe in you.

1005
01:08:43,630 --> 01:08:45,621
50 million!

1006
01:08:49,349 --> 01:08:51,067
I,...

1007
01:08:51,149 --> 01:08:53,458
...Nicholas Leeson,...

1008
01:08:53,549 --> 01:08:55,380
...have lost...

1009
01:08:55,469 --> 01:08:57,460
...50 million quid...

1010
01:08:58,389 --> 01:09:00,379
...in one day!

1011
01:09:05,388 --> 01:09:07,344
What does he do, exactly?

1012
01:09:07,428 --> 01:09:09,895
That's what no one
seems able to explain.

1013
01:09:09,987 --> 01:09:13,696
It's simple. He switches contracts
between Osaka and SIMEX,...

1014
01:09:13,787 --> 01:09:17,063
...exploiting price differentials
between the two markets.

1015
01:09:17,147 --> 01:09:19,979
That's how he offers the best deals
to our customers.

1016
01:09:20,066 --> 01:09:22,819
If it's that easy, why isn't
everybody doing it?

1017
01:09:22,906 --> 01:09:27,377
Because he's absolutely in the vortex
of the information curve over there.

1018
01:09:27,466 --> 01:09:30,377
He's discovered a whole
new way of making money.

1019
01:09:31,025 --> 01:09:35,337
Well, he's giving us horrendous
funding problems, that's all I know.

1020
01:09:36,505 --> 01:09:40,577
He doesn't do things by the book, Ron.
He just doesn't respect the rules.

1021
01:09:40,664 --> 01:09:44,373
Is he really the kind of person
we should be employing at Barings?

1022
01:09:44,464 --> 01:09:49,412
Oh, fuck the rules. It's barrow boys like
Nick who are turning the City around.

1023
01:09:49,503 --> 01:09:53,894
You can't run a modern financial centre
with a bunch of Hooray Henries.

1024
01:09:58,622 --> 01:10:00,021
Bastard!

1025
01:10:00,102 --> 01:10:02,093
Wakey-wakey!

1026
01:10:02,662 --> 01:10:05,017
- What's the action, mate?
- You tell me.

1027
01:10:05,102 --> 01:10:07,979
The market's up and down
like a tart's knickers.

1028
01:10:08,061 --> 01:10:11,258
- I think the worst is over.
- Who knows? You could be right.

1029
01:10:11,341 --> 01:10:13,297
Well, that's my hunch anyway.

1030
01:10:13,381 --> 01:10:15,974
Listen, I was out last
night with that Loy.

1031
01:10:16,060 --> 01:10:18,096
You know, that journo from Reuters.

1032
01:10:18,180 --> 01:10:20,694
He's convinced there's
no mystery customer.

1033
01:10:20,780 --> 01:10:24,409
He reckons it's you. He thinks
you're trading on your own account.

1034
01:10:24,500 --> 01:10:26,455
Without the bank's approval.

1035
01:10:28,659 --> 01:10:30,775
Now, you're not that crazy, are you?

1036
01:10:30,859 --> 01:10:32,736
What do you think?

1037
01:10:32,819 --> 01:10:36,094
Who, then? Beaumarchais?
I thought he'd given you the elbow.

1038
01:10:36,178 --> 01:10:39,329
- I can't tell you.
- Come on. It's me, Danny Boy!

1039
01:10:39,418 --> 01:10:42,728
I could tell you... but I'd
have to shoot you afterwards.

1040
01:10:45,817 --> 01:10:48,490
I know one thing.
If Customer X didn't exist,...

1041
01:10:48,577 --> 01:10:50,613
...you'd have to invent him.

1042
01:10:52,737 --> 01:10:55,375
45 million? You've already
had 100 this week.

1043
01:10:55,456 --> 01:10:59,847
Everybody's had an advance margin call
from SIMEX on their client positions.

1044
01:10:59,936 --> 01:11:03,132
They're worried about stability
with these big movements.

1045
01:11:03,215 --> 01:11:05,206
It's an emergency measure?

1046
01:11:06,335 --> 01:11:08,326
Isn't everybody squealing out there?

1047
01:11:08,415 --> 01:11:11,407
No, we'll get it back when
the market calms down.

1048
01:11:12,455 --> 01:11:15,446
Nick, when are you gonna
reduce these positions?

1049
01:11:15,534 --> 01:11:17,923
The bean counters are freakin' out!

1050
01:11:18,014 --> 01:11:20,448
Ron! Didn't know you were there.

1051
01:11:20,534 --> 01:11:24,128
For fuck's sake, we've had the
Bank of International Settlements...

1052
01:11:24,213 --> 01:11:26,773
...asking if Barings can meet
its margin payments!

1053
01:11:26,853 --> 01:11:30,562
- It is not good for the image!
- I hear you, Ron. It's a tight market.

1054
01:11:30,653 --> 01:11:32,847
Yeah, well,
you've really gotta try.

1055
01:11:32,932 --> 01:11:34,923
Take a hit on it if you have to.

1056
01:11:35,012 --> 01:11:39,290
I know Norris is gonna want to discuss it
with you when he's out there next week.

1057
01:11:39,372 --> 01:11:41,044
Norris?

1058
01:11:41,811 --> 01:11:44,769
- I didn't know he was coming.
- Yeah, with Tony Hawes.

1059
01:11:44,851 --> 01:11:49,163
They want to check the numbers. Iron out
these funding problems once and for all!

1060
01:11:54,450 --> 01:11:58,728
There was no way I could reduce my
positions without the market collapsing.

1061
01:11:58,810 --> 01:12:03,519
By the time they got to Singapore I was in
deeper than ever, faxing Brenda daily,...

1062
01:12:03,609 --> 01:12:06,362
...30, 40 million
dollars at a time.

1063
01:12:07,609 --> 01:12:09,600
They were gonna kill me.

1064
01:12:32,326 --> 01:12:34,317
Lookin' like shit, Nick.

1065
01:12:35,886 --> 01:12:37,956
Lookin' like fuckin' shit, mate.

1066
01:12:45,645 --> 01:12:47,875
- Good evening, sir.
- Good evening.

1067
01:12:54,364 --> 01:12:57,561
His approach shot
sliced into the woods...

1068
01:12:58,643 --> 01:13:01,953
- Nick. There you are.
- I'm sorry I'm a little bit late.

1069
01:13:02,043 --> 01:13:04,762
- What'll you have?
- A beer would be great, thanks.

1070
01:13:04,843 --> 01:13:06,834
Another Tiger, please.

1071
01:13:07,283 --> 01:13:09,273
Nick...

1072
01:13:10,642 --> 01:13:13,918
- How was the market today?
- It stayed between 18,000 and 18,300.

1073
01:13:14,002 --> 01:13:15,993
It's settled after the earthquake.

1074
01:13:16,082 --> 01:13:18,356
Happy with the positions
you're running?

1075
01:13:18,441 --> 01:13:21,831
I'm relaxed. They're March contracts,
so I'll let them expire.

1076
01:13:21,921 --> 01:13:23,639
- Good.
- Thanks.

1077
01:13:25,481 --> 01:13:28,677
Now, we've had a lot of stick...
over funding.

1078
01:13:28,760 --> 01:13:33,038
Brenda Granger tells me we're borrowing
all over Japan to get the funds to you.

1079
01:13:33,120 --> 01:13:35,315
People are beginning to talk, Nick.

1080
01:13:35,400 --> 01:13:37,515
I understand.

1081
01:13:37,599 --> 01:13:39,430
I understand completely.

1082
01:13:39,999 --> 01:13:41,591
Excellent.

1083
01:13:41,679 --> 01:13:43,670
Good man.

1084
01:13:45,479 --> 01:13:49,437
And that was it. That was apparently
all he had to say on the subject...

1085
01:13:49,518 --> 01:13:54,114
...of my enormous exposure causing
so many ulcers throughout Barings.

1086
01:13:54,198 --> 01:13:56,950
Better than you get in London,
that's for sure!

1087
01:13:57,037 --> 01:13:58,914
You'll enjoy the next course.

1088
01:13:58,997 --> 01:14:01,989
- Lobster, sir?
- No, thanks. I'm not very hungry.

1089
01:14:02,077 --> 01:14:04,715
I should have been able
to relax after that,...

1090
01:14:04,796 --> 01:14:09,153
...but I couldn't stop thinking about
the losses in the five eights account.

1091
01:14:09,236 --> 01:14:11,750
Shame you can't stay for
the match on Saturday.

1092
01:14:16,715 --> 01:14:18,706
You're down for 450, aren't you?

1093
01:14:20,715 --> 01:14:22,785
Your bonus.

1094
01:14:22,875 --> 01:14:24,910
Only a week to go.

1095
01:14:26,514 --> 01:14:27,947
Sorry?

1096
01:14:28,034 --> 01:14:32,550
Have you thought about what you're
going to do with it? Only a week to go!

1097
01:14:37,073 --> 01:14:40,065
Ahem! Excuse me. I have
an announcement to make.

1098
01:14:42,753 --> 01:14:46,665
I know that some of you are worried
about our exposure in the market,...

1099
01:14:46,752 --> 01:14:51,667
...and you're probably wondering about
the identity of our mystery Customer X.

1100
01:14:52,471 --> 01:14:54,860
Well, the fact is...

1101
01:14:54,951 --> 01:14:56,942
...he doesn't exist.

1102
01:14:57,711 --> 01:14:59,941
We are the customer: Barings.

1103
01:15:00,031 --> 01:15:02,544
Look properly at
the five eights account -

1104
01:15:02,630 --> 01:15:05,906
...which is not a client account,
it's an errors account -

1105
01:15:05,990 --> 01:15:10,541
...and you'll realise it's concealing
losses in the region of 200 million.

1106
01:15:11,230 --> 01:15:15,188
No, I tell a lie.
It's more like 230 after today!

1107
01:15:26,148 --> 01:15:29,185
What are you going to do
with all that money, Nick?

1108
01:15:36,507 --> 01:15:39,021
Well, I won't spend it
on futures and options!

1109
01:15:42,986 --> 01:15:44,942
- That's very good.
- Very good.

1110
01:15:51,825 --> 01:15:54,862
I was living from day to day,
hoping for a miracle.

1111
01:15:56,505 --> 01:16:00,383
I wasn't running a position any more.
The position was running me.

1112
01:16:01,984 --> 01:16:05,101
Man, look at the state you're in.
You got the bloody shakes!

1113
01:16:05,184 --> 01:16:07,823
- You been on the razz all night?
- Nah.

1114
01:16:07,904 --> 01:16:11,054
- I'm just getting killed by the market.
- Tell me about it!

1115
01:16:11,143 --> 01:16:13,134
I've had a shitty week too.

1116
01:16:15,663 --> 01:16:17,654
Penguin?
You lucky sod!

1117
01:16:18,423 --> 01:16:20,378
Do you know how rare they are?

1118
01:16:20,462 --> 01:16:22,453
Do you know?

1119
01:16:26,622 --> 01:16:29,693
- It ain't that bloody funny!
- Lucky Leeson!

1120
01:16:29,781 --> 01:16:32,534
You have it. I'm not
laughing at you, Bubble.

1121
01:16:34,381 --> 01:16:36,372
Fuck! Sorry.

1122
01:16:37,940 --> 01:16:41,296
'Ey-ey-ey-ey-ey! You really
are in a bad way, ain't ya?

1123
01:16:42,100 --> 01:16:43,931
What's the matter?

1124
01:16:46,580 --> 01:16:48,649
I have an unauthorised position.

1125
01:16:52,819 --> 01:16:54,810
Fuckin' hell.

1126
01:16:55,819 --> 01:16:57,217
How big?

1127
01:16:58,298 --> 01:17:00,289
Big enough to be a problem.

1128
01:17:01,818 --> 01:17:03,490
Poor bastard!

1129
01:17:03,578 --> 01:17:06,410
I can't say it comes as
a complete surprise.

1130
01:17:06,497 --> 01:17:08,727
- Does Lisa know?
- No, she'd kill me.

1131
01:17:09,617 --> 01:17:14,133
She's got enough on her plate. She's just
waiting for my bonus so we can go home!

1132
01:17:14,217 --> 01:17:16,207
So what are you gonna do?

1133
01:17:17,896 --> 01:17:22,253
Well... I just have to keep buying
futures to support the market.

1134
01:17:22,336 --> 01:17:25,219
If it sticks at 18,000,
my options are still in the money...

1135
01:17:25,545 --> 01:17:27,416
I could get the position back.

1136
01:17:27,575 --> 01:17:30,294
- I may even come out ahead.
- Nick...

1137
01:17:30,375 --> 01:17:32,331
You listen to me now, right.

1138
01:17:32,415 --> 01:17:34,406
You don't fight the market, man.

1139
01:17:34,495 --> 01:17:38,806
Even if you can make the margin calls,
what happens when the contracts expire?

1140
01:17:38,894 --> 01:17:42,523
The way the market's going,
your losses could be catastrophic!

1141
01:18:07,691 --> 01:18:10,410
Five for a thousand,
five for a thousand! Come on!

1142
01:18:10,491 --> 01:18:14,563
George, move this fuckin' market!
If it stays below 18,000 we're dead!

1143
01:18:23,969 --> 01:18:25,960
Come on!

1144
01:18:43,007 --> 01:18:43,996
Nick.

1145
01:18:45,527 --> 01:18:47,836
- Nick!
- Tony.

1146
01:18:47,927 --> 01:18:51,397
Nick, I really need to go over
some of the figures with you.

1147
01:18:51,486 --> 01:18:53,477
Sure, Tony.

1148
01:18:57,406 --> 01:18:59,044
Back in a minute.

1149
01:19:02,725 --> 01:19:04,716
Seven for five!
Seven for five!

1150
01:19:11,924 --> 01:19:13,642
I'm sorry. Money!

1151
01:20:00,439 --> 01:20:04,352
I'd thrown away countless more millions,
and it hadn't made a dent.

1152
01:20:04,439 --> 01:20:07,953
I was only one day from bonus day,
but the game was up.

1153
01:20:09,518 --> 01:20:11,509
I was beaten.

1154
01:20:48,834 --> 01:20:51,507
Oh, Nick, you're a
bloody fool, aren't you?

1155
01:20:52,874 --> 01:20:57,344
Well, it's not the end of the world.
You've got your health, you've got me...

1156
01:20:57,433 --> 01:20:59,389
Shame about the bonus.

1157
01:20:59,473 --> 01:21:01,464
Sorry.

1158
01:21:02,073 --> 01:21:04,428
Slow down.
The video shop's on the next left.

1159
01:21:04,513 --> 01:21:06,662
- I wanna get our deposit back.
- Right.

1160
01:21:06,752 --> 01:21:08,902
We're gonna need it, darlin'.

1161
01:21:23,671 --> 01:21:26,662
- Hello?
- The positions have got bigger!

1162
01:21:26,750 --> 01:21:30,106
If they aren't reduced
I'm coming out there to sort you out!

1163
01:21:30,190 --> 01:21:33,307
- You're very faint, Ron.
- And what's this rumour I hear?

1164
01:21:33,390 --> 01:21:35,698
There's a rumour that
we're the customer.

1165
01:21:35,789 --> 01:21:37,859
Sorry, you're gonna
have to speak up.

1166
01:21:37,949 --> 01:21:40,224
Tell me we're not
the customer, Nick.

1167
01:21:40,309 --> 01:21:43,381
- I'm losing you, Ron.
- Nick! Nick, are you there?

1168
01:21:43,468 --> 01:21:45,459
Goodbye, Ron.

1169
01:21:48,628 --> 01:21:51,859
They wouldn't give me the full 200,
but I stood my ground and got 180.

1170
01:21:51,948 --> 01:21:53,938
Good girl.

1171
01:21:58,067 --> 01:21:59,659
Nick...!

1172
01:22:27,944 --> 01:22:30,378
Excuse me, sir.
There's a phone call for you.

1173
01:22:30,464 --> 01:22:33,455
- Not now. - It's Peter Norris.
He said it's urgent.

1174
01:22:33,543 --> 01:22:35,101
Oh. Thank you.

1175
01:22:35,183 --> 01:22:37,014
Would you excuse me?

1176
01:22:47,382 --> 01:22:48,701
Peter?

1177
01:22:48,782 --> 01:22:51,818
I'm sorry to drag you away
from your dinner party.

1178
01:22:52,821 --> 01:22:55,540
I'm afraid I've got some
rather bad news.

1179
01:22:57,821 --> 01:23:02,291
By the time the shit hit the proverbial fan
in London we'd escaped Singapore...

1180
01:23:02,380 --> 01:23:05,338
...to ponder the future
and consider my options.

1181
01:23:05,420 --> 01:23:07,297
If I had any.

1182
01:23:08,260 --> 01:23:10,250
What's gonna happen, Nick?

1183
01:23:10,979 --> 01:23:14,813
They must have got my fax and
closed down all the positions on Friday.

1184
01:23:14,899 --> 01:23:17,015
The market seems to
be holding up OK.

1185
01:23:17,099 --> 01:23:19,248
But you're definitely out of a job?

1186
01:23:22,258 --> 01:23:26,297
It could have been a lot worse,
but I still lost them a ton of money.

1187
01:23:28,258 --> 01:23:30,566
I'm starving! Think they
do burgers here?

1188
01:23:30,657 --> 01:23:32,932
No! You're not having a burger.

1189
01:23:33,017 --> 01:23:36,771
- That tummy of yours is driving me nuts.
- Don't stress me, wench!

1190
01:23:38,496 --> 01:23:40,487
I'll work it off in the gym.

1191
01:23:43,296 --> 01:23:45,287
Better still...

1192
01:23:51,335 --> 01:23:55,294
- Stop it. People are watching.
- So? I don't care. Come here, girl.

1193
01:24:00,574 --> 01:24:01,973
Jesus Christ, Lisa!

1194
01:24:03,814 --> 01:24:06,169
- Barings has gone bust!
- What?!

1195
01:24:08,453 --> 01:24:11,445
The Chancellor of the Exchequer
is trying to calm fears...

1196
01:24:11,533 --> 01:24:15,321
...sparked by the failure of Barings Bank.
In a statement to Parliament...

1197
01:24:15,413 --> 01:24:19,121
...he denied reports that the British
banking system is about to collapse.

1198
01:24:19,212 --> 01:24:23,046
According to him, Barings'
failure is a unique situation,...

1199
01:24:23,132 --> 01:24:26,840
...which he blames on the actions
of a rogue trader in Singapore.

1200
01:24:26,931 --> 01:24:32,403
Estimates of potential losses range from
800 million to over one billion pounds.

1201
01:24:32,491 --> 01:24:36,608
There's no way of knowing how markets
will react when they reopen on Monday.

1202
01:24:36,690 --> 01:24:40,080
As the Bank of England tries to
put together a rescue package,...

1203
01:24:40,170 --> 01:24:44,607
...with the Sultan of Brunei rumoured
as a buyer, time may be running out...

1204
01:24:44,690 --> 01:24:48,204
...for one of Britain's most
venerable financial institutions.

1205
01:24:48,289 --> 01:24:50,564
Charles Samson, CNN, London.

1206
01:24:50,649 --> 01:24:52,640
Fuck!

1207
01:24:53,609 --> 01:24:55,485
Oh, Nick!

1208
01:25:01,168 --> 01:25:03,124
How could you not tell me?

1209
01:25:03,208 --> 01:25:06,836
How could you have kept it hidden
for all this time, Nick?

1210
01:25:09,167 --> 01:25:11,123
You must have been through hell!

1211
01:25:11,207 --> 01:25:14,482
You would have marched me
straight into Simon Jones's office.

1212
01:25:14,566 --> 01:25:17,000
- Too bloody right!
- Then I'd have got fired,...

1213
01:25:17,086 --> 01:25:20,522
...and I couldn't have made the money
back. That's all I was gonna do.

1214
01:25:20,606 --> 01:25:22,801
No, but you were gambling.

1215
01:25:22,886 --> 01:25:26,321
That's what you were doing.
With other people's money.

1216
01:25:27,565 --> 01:25:29,715
I didn't want to let everyone down.

1217
01:25:31,405 --> 01:25:34,521
You, my dad, the girls in the office...

1218
01:25:37,364 --> 01:25:39,355
Even Ron bloody Baker!

1219
01:25:42,803 --> 01:25:45,522
Do you think they're all
gonna hate me now?

1220
01:25:45,603 --> 01:25:48,515
Well, I don't think you're
gonna be Mr Popular!

1221
01:25:51,883 --> 01:25:54,396
It could easily have been
the other way, you know.

1222
01:25:55,442 --> 01:25:57,433
It so nearly was.

1223
01:25:59,002 --> 01:26:00,993
Then I'd be a hero.

1224
01:26:03,001 --> 01:26:04,912
Oh...!

1225
01:26:05,001 --> 01:26:07,071
Come here.
Come here.

1226
01:26:11,080 --> 01:26:13,071
I still love ya. Mm?

1227
01:26:14,600 --> 01:26:17,637
- I love you very much.
- I love you too.

1228
01:26:25,359 --> 01:26:29,034
Shall we see if I can do
something about that belly?

1229
01:26:29,119 --> 01:26:31,109
I see.

1230
01:26:32,398 --> 01:26:34,229
Yes, I understand.

1231
01:26:34,318 --> 01:26:36,434
No, of course.

1232
01:26:37,118 --> 01:26:39,313
Thank you again for your efforts.

1233
01:26:39,398 --> 01:26:40,796
Goodbye.

1234
01:26:43,557 --> 01:26:47,470
That was the Sultan of Brunei's office.
They have decided not to proceed.

1235
01:26:47,557 --> 01:26:51,868
They believe the risks are too great and
the time too short, in view of the need...

1236
01:26:51,956 --> 01:26:56,393
...to have a rescue package ready by the
time markets open again in the Far East.

1237
01:26:56,476 --> 01:26:58,467
Is there really no one else?

1238
01:26:59,115 --> 01:27:01,504
We've tried everyone.
It's hopeless.

1239
01:27:03,835 --> 01:27:07,714
I therefore have to inform you
that Barings is insolvent...

1240
01:27:07,795 --> 01:27:10,467
.,.and will go into
immediate liquidation.

1241
01:27:16,994 --> 01:27:21,145
Peter Barings has gone on TV
and said there's been a conspiracy.

1242
01:27:21,233 --> 01:27:22,951
They've lost 800 million quid!

1243
01:27:23,033 --> 01:27:25,501
I lost nowhere near that.
It was more like 300!

1244
01:27:25,593 --> 01:27:29,983
But Barings didn't do anything Friday.
Now the word's out, the market's crashed.

1245
01:27:30,072 --> 01:27:31,585
Bloody idiots!

1246
01:27:31,672 --> 01:27:33,663
They think you've run
off on your yacht.

1247
01:27:33,752 --> 01:27:35,788
- What?!
- I know. But listen, mate.

1248
01:27:35,872 --> 01:27:39,307
You've got no friends here now,
so just get the fuck out of Asia.

1249
01:27:39,391 --> 01:27:42,144
Get back to London, Australia, anywhere.
Just get out.

1250
01:27:42,231 --> 01:27:43,789
We're tryin'.

1251
01:27:43,871 --> 01:27:47,226
Oi, Nick... get yourself
a good lawyer.

1252
01:27:47,310 --> 01:27:49,301
- Be lucky.
- Cheers, mate.

1253
01:27:50,030 --> 01:27:52,180
Flight 187 to Hong Kong...

1254
01:27:52,270 --> 01:27:54,261
...leaving from gate two.

1255
01:27:56,669 --> 01:27:57,897
Fuck!

1256
01:28:05,429 --> 01:28:09,865
There's a manhunt all over Asia. They
think we're sailing around in our yacht!

1257
01:28:09,948 --> 01:28:13,497
- What bloody yacht?
- I know. What about the flights?

1258
01:28:13,588 --> 01:28:16,704
- There's one to London. Via Singapore.
- That's no good.

1259
01:28:16,787 --> 01:28:19,460
There's a flight to Frankfurt.
Via Abu Dhabi.

1260
01:28:19,547 --> 01:28:21,105
Let's take it.

1261
01:28:21,187 --> 01:28:22,859
And Lisa...

1262
01:28:22,947 --> 01:28:24,937
Pay cash.

1263
01:29:13,421 --> 01:29:15,537
- Newspaper, sir?
- No, thank you.

1264
01:29:15,621 --> 01:29:17,612
- Ma'am?
- Er... no, thanks.

1265
01:29:21,061 --> 01:29:23,096
Nick, take that thing off.

1266
01:29:23,180 --> 01:29:26,092
There's a guy over
there lookin' at me.

1267
01:29:26,180 --> 01:29:28,648
I'm not surprised,
with that bloody hat on!

1268
01:29:28,740 --> 01:29:33,130
Talk about conspicuous! You're
sticking out like a sore bloody thumb.

1269
01:29:34,539 --> 01:29:36,734
Did you say we stop at Abu Dhabi?

1270
01:29:36,819 --> 01:29:39,049
Yeah.

1271
01:29:39,139 --> 01:29:43,177
- That's where they cut your hands off.
- Oh, don't be ridiculous!

1272
01:29:44,018 --> 01:29:46,009
They just stone you.

1273
01:29:47,138 --> 01:29:49,368
What?

1274
01:29:49,458 --> 01:29:51,607
I'm sorry, but you've gotta laugh!

1275
01:29:53,777 --> 01:29:58,567
Poor old Barings, eh? That's what you get
for hiring the wrong sort of person.

1276
01:30:12,735 --> 01:30:15,203
That was when it hit me -

1277
01:30:15,295 --> 01:30:17,286
...the enormity of what I'd done.

1278
01:30:18,135 --> 01:30:21,968
Whatever happened, I knew things
were never gonna be the same again.

1279
01:30:22,054 --> 01:30:24,727
And I've never felt
lonelier in all my life.

1280
01:30:33,813 --> 01:30:36,043
I love you, Lisa.

1281
01:30:36,133 --> 01:30:38,124
Whatever happens, I love you.

1282
01:30:38,772 --> 01:30:40,763
I love you too.

1283
01:30:41,732 --> 01:30:43,723
I've got to get back to London.

1284
01:30:44,452 --> 01:30:49,764
I couldn't stand being in jail in Singapore.
I couldn't stand it if I couldn't see you.

1285
01:30:54,851 --> 01:30:56,842
Jesus Christ, it's the police!

1286
01:30:56,931 --> 01:30:58,966
They must know I'm on the flight.

1287
01:30:59,050 --> 01:31:01,280
Well... no, not necessarily.

1288
01:31:02,170 --> 01:31:07,687
Due to our early arrival, passport control
will take place as you leave the plane.

1289
01:31:07,769 --> 01:31:09,839
Please have your documents ready.

1290
01:31:11,329 --> 01:31:12,444
See?

1291
01:31:16,009 --> 01:31:17,999
I'm scared, Lisa!

1292
01:31:19,568 --> 01:31:21,559
You be strong, OK?

1293
01:31:29,727 --> 01:31:31,126
Danke.

1294
01:31:32,207 --> 01:31:33,925
Pass, bitte.

1295
01:31:34,007 --> 01:31:36,679
Danke. Thank you.

1296
01:31:38,566 --> 01:31:40,557
Please show your passport.

1297
01:31:43,726 --> 01:31:45,603
Where is your man?

1298
01:31:47,525 --> 01:31:49,516
I'm her man.

1299
01:32:10,843 --> 01:32:14,040
250 bid on 100! 250
bid on 100! Come on!

1300
01:32:14,123 --> 01:32:17,956
Who wants some of that? 250 bid
on 100! 250 bid on 100! Come on!

1301
01:32:35,920 --> 01:32:39,276
And that's it, more or less.
That's the end of my story.

